---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Baltimore Wedding Planner"
  description="How Baltimore Wedding Planner collects, uses, and protects your personal information. GDPR and CCPA compliant privacy practices."
  canonical="https://baltimoreweddingplanner.com/privacy-policy"
  noindex={true}
>
  <div class="container">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Privacy Policy' }]} />
  </div>

  <section class="section bg-[#FAF7F5]">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">

      <div class="mb-10">
        <h1 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold text-stone-900 tracking-tight mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm font-body">Effective Date: June 4, 2026 | Last Updated: June 4, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-stone max-w-none font-body text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed space-y-8">

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>Baltimore Wedding Planner ("we," "us," or "our") operates baltimoreweddingplanner.com. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information when you visit our website or contact us about our wedding planning services.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">By using our website, you agree to the practices described in this policy. If you don't agree, please don't use our site.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">2. Information We Collect</h2>

          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-2">2.1 Information You Provide Directly</h3>
          <p>When you contact us through our website, we collect:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>Your name (first and last)</li>
            <li>Email address</li>
            <li>Phone number (optional)</li>
            <li>Wedding date or estimated date</li>
            <li>Approximate wedding budget range</li>
            <li>Service interest (which service you're inquiring about)</li>
            <li>Any message or notes you include</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">When you book a consultation through Calendly, Calendly collects your name, email, and scheduling preferences according to their own Privacy Policy.</p>

          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-2 mt-5">2.2 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
          <p>When you visit our website, we and our third-party analytics providers automatically collect:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>IP address (anonymized in Google Analytics 4)</li>
            <li>Browser type and version</li>
            <li>Device type and operating system</li>
            <li>Pages you visit and time spent on each page</li>
            <li>Referring website or search terms</li>
            <li>Geographic region (city or country level)</li>
            <li>Session recordings and heatmaps (Microsoft Clarity)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p>We use your information to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>Respond to your consultation inquiries within 24 hours</li>
            <li>Schedule and conduct free consultations</li>
            <li>Provide wedding planning services you hire us for</li>
            <li>Send service-related communications (confirmations, updates)</li>
            <li>Improve our website and services using anonymized analytics data</li>
            <li>Comply with applicable laws and regulations</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">We do not use your information for automated decision-making or profiling. We do not sell your personal information to any third party.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">4. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)</h2>
          <p>If you are located in the European Union or European Economic Area, our legal basis for processing your information is:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li><strong>Consent:</strong> For analytics cookies and optional marketing communications</li>
            <li><strong>Contract performance:</strong> For delivering wedding planning services you have engaged us for</li>
            <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> For responding to inquiries, improving our website, and preventing fraud</li>
            <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> For maintaining records required by applicable law</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">5. How We Share Your Information</h2>
          <p>We share your information only with the following third parties who process data on our behalf:</p>

          <div class="mt-3 overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
              <thead>
                <tr class="bg-stone-100">
                  <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-stone-900 border border-stone-200">Service</th>
                  <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-stone-900 border border-stone-200">Purpose</th>
                  <th class="text-left p-3 font-semibold text-stone-900 border border-stone-200">Data Shared</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="font-body">
                <tr><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Google Analytics 4</td><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Website usage analytics</td><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Anonymized usage data</td></tr>
                <tr class="bg-stone-50"><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Microsoft Clarity</td><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Heatmaps and session recordings</td><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Anonymized session data</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Netlify Forms</td><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Contact form processing</td><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Form submission data</td></tr>
                <tr class="bg-stone-50"><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Calendly</td><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Consultation scheduling</td><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Name, email, time preferences</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Google Fonts</td><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">Website typography</td><td class="p-3 border border-stone-200">IP address (technical)</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-4">We may also disclose your information if required by law, subpoena, or court order, or to protect the rights, property, or safety of our business or others.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">6. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
          <p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies on our website. For detailed information about the specific cookies we use and how to manage them, please see our <a href="/cookie-policy" class="text-[#C89481] hover:underline">Cookie Policy</a>.</p>
          <p class="mt-3">You can manage your cookie preferences through our cookie consent banner or your browser settings at any time.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">7. Your Privacy Rights</h2>

          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-2">7.1 GDPR Rights (EU/UK Visitors)</h3>
          <p>If you are in the EU or UK, you have the right to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
            <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data ("right to be forgotten")</li>
            <li>Restrict or object to certain processing</li>
            <li>Receive your data in a portable format</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent at any time (where processing is based on consent)</li>
            <li>Lodge a complaint with your national data protection authority</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-2 mt-5">7.2 CCPA Rights (California Residents)</h3>
          <p>If you are a California resident, you have the right to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>Know what personal information we collect, use, disclose, or sell</li>
            <li>Delete personal information we have collected about you</li>
            <li>Correct inaccurate personal information</li>
            <li>Opt out of the sale of personal information (we do not sell personal information)</li>
            <li>Non-discrimination for exercising your rights</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-2 mt-5">7.3 How to Exercise Your Rights</h3>
          <p>To exercise any of these rights, email us at <a href="mailto:john@baltimoreweddingplanner.com" class="text-[#C89481] hover:underline">john@baltimoreweddingplanner.com</a> with the subject line "Privacy Request." We will respond within 30 days. We may ask you to verify your identity before fulfilling requests.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">8. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>We retain your personal information only as long as necessary:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm">
            <li>Consultation inquiries that don't become clients: 12 months from last contact</li>
            <li>Client records: duration of service relationship plus 7 years (for tax and business records)</li>
            <li>Analytics data: 14 months (Google Analytics 4 default)</li>
            <li>Session recordings: 30 days (Microsoft Clarity default)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">9. Data Security</h2>
          <p>We implement reasonable security measures including SSL/TLS encryption for data in transit, access controls limiting who can access your data, and secure hosting through Vercel. However, no internet transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">10. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>Our services are intended for adults planning weddings. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 16. If you believe we have inadvertently collected information from a child, please contact us immediately.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will update the "Last Updated" date above when changes are made. Your continued use of our website after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mb-3">12. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>For questions about this Privacy Policy or to exercise your rights:</p>
          <div class="mt-3 bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded-2xl p-5 text-sm">
            <p><strong class="text-stone-900">Baltimore Wedding Planner</strong></p>
            <p>John (Lead Planner)</p>
            <p>Baltimore, Maryland, USA</p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:john@baltimoreweddingplanner.com" class="text-[#C89481] hover:underline">john@baltimoreweddingplanner.com</a></p>
            <p>Phone: <a href="tel:+14105550100" class="text-[#C89481] hover:underline">(410) 555-0100</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
